==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hibernate
<hw>Hi"ber*nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Hibernated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Hibernating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>hibernare</ets>, <ets>hibernatum</ets>, fr. <ets>hibernus</ets>
wintry. See <er>Hibernal</er>.]</ety> <def>To winter; to pass the season
of winter in close quarters, in a torpid or lethargic state, as certain
mammals, reptiles, and insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Inclination would lead me to <qex>hibernate</qex>, during half the
year, in this uncomfortable climate of Great Britain.</q>
<rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hibernating</ent>⟦br⟧
